JUnit and JTest are complementary and not competing tools.

Try to get at least one fact straight.

So said javainsel on 4/4/2003 --------------------
I have not used JTest, but I do not see it as a substitute.
> Regards,
> David

It seems that it includes and substitutes JUnit and has more features 
than JUnit. And it seems to automate testing as far as possible, thus 
making testing more productive.
